# CLAUDE.md (Global)

This file applies to all Claude Code sessions, across all projects.

## Agent workflow

When the user says "并发执行任务" or similar, do NOT launch sub-agents directly. Instead:
1. Confirm the concurrency plan (task breakdown, parallelism dependencies, which agent per task)
2. Confirm constraints for each sub-agent
3. Confirm acceptance criteria for each sub-agent
4. Start execution only after user explicitly confirms
If a sub-agent fails the same task 3 times, stop retrying and report to the user.

When the user corrects a mistake, proactively ask whether to update the relevant configuration to prevent recurrence.

When the user runs `/compact`, proactively ask whether to extract constraints from the current conversation context and update project-level or global configuration.

## Tool Preferences

- Prefer Read, Edit, Write, Glob, Grep over Bash for file operations
- Use `/browse` from gstack for all web browsing. Never use `mcp__claude-in-chrome__*` tools.

## Communication

- Language: Chinese for discussion, English for code
- Direct, concrete, builder-to-builder tone
- No emojis unless explicitly requested
- Reference code as `file:line_number`

## Code Style

- No comments for WHAT code does — well-named identifiers already do that
- Comments only for non-obvious WHY
- No half-finished implementations
- Default to editing existing files; prefer simple over abstract

## Safety

- Never update git config
- Never skip hooks unless user explicitly asks
- Never force push to main/master
- Always create NEW commits (not amend) unless explicitly asked
